Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, high protein, ketones, and glucose). There is also hypoglycemia and low HbA1c, with metabolic acidosis suggested by low CO₂. These findings are consistent with advanced kidney disease, possible nephrotic syndrome, and metabolic derangements. Immediate clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
